Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
Deacon Trading Estate is a well established estate located at the top end of Chickenhall Lane at its junction with Tower Lane.  Junctions 12 and 13 of the M3 and junction 5 of the M27 are all within approximately 1.75 miles.

Eastleigh itself is a well established industrial location with the town centre located approximately 6 miles to the north of Southampton, 14 miles to the west of Portsmouth and 10 miles to the south of Winchester.

Unit C3 forms part of a terrace and have been refurbished to a high standard.  The units provide open warehouse space with ground and first floor offices and benefit from car parking/yard areas to the front.  They are steel portal frame construction with part brick and part profile metal sheet elevations. 

Accommodation Specification:-

Warehouse 4,398 sq ft

Ground/First Floor Offices 580 sq ft

Eastleigh is a well-established industrial location with the town centre located approximately 6 miles to the north of Southampton City Centre and 8 miles to the south of Winchester. Eastleigh Station is approximately ½ a mile from the site providing direct access to London Waterloo with a journey time of approximately 1 hour.

The property comprises a semi-detached two bay industrial / warehouse with an external yard measuring 16,998 sq ft and nearby dedicated parking.

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
Location

The site is located off Dutton Lane with links to the B3037 Bishopstoke Road. The Bishopstoke Road provides access to Eastleigh Town Centre and Southampton Road linking to Eastleigh Railway Station, Southampton Parkway Station, Southampton International Airport and Junction 5 of the M27. To the North it links with the Romsey Road linking to Leigh Road and Junction 13 of the M3 motorway.

Description 

The site comprises an area of approximately 1.9 acres in an irregular shape with a single access point off Dutton Lane.

Note: The site has permission for Open Storage, with an hours of use restriction whereby the occupier shall not operate except between the hours of 08:00 hours and 17:00 Hours and no deliveries shall be received or dispatched from the site except between the hours of 08:30 hours and 16:30 hours.

Key Benefits

Fully fenced & gated secure site
Convenient town centre location
Excellent Transport Link to M3 & M27

Location

The property is situated on Goodwood Road at the head of the Boyatt Wood Industrial Estate. There are excellent transport links with junction 13 of the M3 Motorway being a 3-minute drive away via Woodside Avenue.

Description

A fully refurbished end of terrace unit on the established Boyatt Wood Industrial Estate in Eastleigh. Peacock Trading Estate comprises a modern terrace of industrial/trade units with good prominence from Goodwood Road. Unit 1 has recently been comprehensively refurbished to the following;

+ Steel portal frame construction
+ Large clear span warehouse area
+ Brick and cladding elevations
+ Large loading apron
+ New steel roof
+ LED lighting throughout
+ 5.82m min eaves
+ Ground ﬂoor ofﬁces
+ Fully Refurbished
+ EPC Rating C 55
